description: Shaved brussels sprouts and creamy feta make this frittata a tasty and easy lunch or dinner option.
name: Brussels Sprout & Feta Frittata Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat the oven to 200Â°C. Heat the oil in a large, oven-proof pan on medium heat and cook the brussels sprouts and spring onions for 5 minutes. Stir in the garlic and cook for 2 minutes.

Whisk the eggs, half of the feta and cracked black pepper together in a bowl an pour over the brussels sprout mix. Dot the rest of the feta on top. Cook for 34 minutes until just set around the edges.
Place the pan into the oven and cook for 1012 minutes until set.
